properties.name: END1
properties.label: Endpoint_1
properties.text: The proportion of patients achieving treatment success defined as either an increase in PG to >70 mg/dL or an increase of >20 mg/dL from nadir within 30 minutes after administration of glucagon. The nadir is defined as the minimum PG value at the time of or within 10 minutes following glucagon administration.

properties.name: OBJ1
properties.label: Objective_1
properties.text: To demonstrate that 3 mg LY900018 is non-inferior to 1 mg IMG for the proportion of patients achieving treatment success from insulin-induced hypoglycemia using a non-inferiority margin of 10%

properties.name: END2
properties.label: Endpoint_2
properties.text:
SAE, TEAEs (including gastrointestinal, nasal,
and non-nasal AEs), vital signs

properties.name: OBJ2
properties.label: Objective_2
properties.text: To compare the safety and tolerability of 3 mg LY900018 with 1 mg IMG

properties.name: END3

properties.name: OBJ3
